<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Colonial brachycnemic zoantharians with heavily sand-incrusted ectoderm and mesoglea. Occasionally solitary polyps are also seen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Various authors have suggested to include the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Protopalythoa</taxonomicName>
Verrill, 1900 over the past century based on both morphological (
<bibRefCitation author="Pax, F" editor="Spengel, JW" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="157 - 330" title="Studien an westindischen Actinien." volume="11" volumeTitle="Ergebnisse einer Zoologischen Forschungreise nach Westindien von Prof. W. Kukenthal und Dr R. Hartmeyer im Jahre, 1907." year="1910">Pax 1910</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ryland, JS" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="407 - 428" title="Revision of methods for separating species of Protopalythoa (Hexacorallia: Zoanthidea) in the tropical West Pacific." url="10.1071/IS02008" volume="17" year="2003">Ryland and Lancaster 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Burnett, WJ" journalOrPublisher="Coral Reefs" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="55 - 68" title="Zoanthids (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Great Barrier Reef and Torres Strait, Australia: systematics, evolution and a key to species." url="10.1007/s003380050060" volume="16" year="1997">Burnett et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reimer, JD" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="87 - 94" title="Molecular evidence suggesting species in the zoanthid genera Palythoa and Protopalythoa (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) are congeneric." url="10.2108/zsj.23.87" volume="23" year="2006 a">Reimer et al. 2006a</bibRefCitation>
). Polyps of 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Palythoa</taxonomicName>
are embedded in a well-developed coenenchyme (= 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“immersae”">&quot;immersae&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pax, F" editor="Spengel, JW" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="157 - 330" title="Studien an westindischen Actinien." volume="11" volumeTitle="Ergebnisse einer Zoologischen Forschungreise nach Westindien von Prof. W. Kukenthal und Dr R. Hartmeyer im Jahre, 1907." year="1910">Pax 1910</bibRefCitation>
) while those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Protopalythoa</taxonomicName>
are more free and clear of the coenenchyme (= 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“intermediate”">&quot;intermediate&quot;</normalizedToken>
or 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“liberae”">&quot;liberae&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pax, F" editor="Spengel, JW" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="157 - 330" title="Studien an westindischen Actinien." volume="11" volumeTitle="Ergebnisse einer Zoologischen Forschungreise nach Westindien von Prof. W. Kukenthal und Dr R. Hartmeyer im Jahre, 1907." year="1910">Pax 1910</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, we consider 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Protopalythoa</taxonomicName>
to be included within 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Palythoa</taxonomicName>
. In general, polyps are firmly attached to stones or reef rocks. Currently, approximately 130 nominal species have been described (
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Palythoa</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Protopalythoa</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reimer, JD" journalOrPublisher="Galaxea" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="World Register of Marine Species" url="http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&amp;id=205785" year="2014 b">Reimer 2014b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reimer, JD" journalOrPublisher="Galaxea" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="World Register of Marine Species" url="http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&amp;id=100795" year="2014 c">c</bibRefCitation>
) although some studies have suggested the presence of many synonyms (
<bibRefCitation author="Burnett, WJ" journalOrPublisher="Coral Reefs" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="55 - 68" title="Zoanthids (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Great Barrier Reef and Torres Strait, Australia: systematics, evolution and a key to species." url="10.1007/s003380050060" volume="16" year="1997">Burnett et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reimer, JD" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="517 - 525" title="Reconsidering Zoanthus spp. diversity: molecular evidence of conspecificity within four previously presumed species." url="10.2108/zsj.21.517" volume="21" year="2004">Reimer et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reimer, JD" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Marine Biology" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="Species diversity of shallow water zoanthids (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) in Florida." url="10.1155/2012/856079" volume="2012" year="2012 a">Reimer et al. 2012a</bibRefCitation>
). All described species are zooxanthellate with the exception of 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa macmurrichi" order="Zoantharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="macmurrichi">Palythoa macmurrichi</taxonomicName>
(Haddon &amp; Shackleton, 1891) (see Remarks below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
